sub_title: President of UNION-IP - Dutch and European Patent Attorney at WijnstraWise Patents
summary:
Reinier Wijnstra is the owner and director of WijnstraWise B.V. He is a European and Dutch patent attorney with more than 20 years of experience in IP, and an official Representative before the Unified Patent Court (UPC). 
Reinier is also President of the Union of European Practioners in Intellectual Property (UNION-IP).
The aims of WijnstraWise are to help companies during the development phase of a new product, by mapping the opportunities and risks of patents, providing effective patent protection, as well as to assist after the launch of a product by defending clients’ rights in and outside courts. 
Reinier represents clients before the Dutch and European Patent Office, before Dutch courts in patent and know how cases, and before the UPC. He is Vice President of Union-IP, and member of the Main Standing Advisory Committee of the European Patent Office (EPO). He is a member of the Dutch Association of Patent Attorneys and the EPI. Reinier is a regular speaker and moderator at IP conferences.
